\begin_layout Standard
Similar to the previous case, we once again consider the situation where
 the adhesive pad is pulled vertically upwards for detachment.
 However now, the leg is assumed to be hinged freely to the array.
 In this case, the array will reorient itself such that the net torque about
 the hinge remains zero during the entire detachment process.
 At any given instant, the tilt angle, 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

, can be found by setting 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{net}$
\end_inset

 to zero in equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:moment_n_d"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 to get:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
