\begin_inset Formula $N_{c}=10$
\end_inset

) snaps off.
 No such force drop is seen when 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta=6\textdegree$
\end_inset

, because 
\begin_inset Formula $N_{c}$
\end_inset

 is less than 1 (equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:prop_nc"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

).
 All its hairs have already detached sequentially before it could trigger
 a spontaneous detachment.
 So in this case, the force-distance curves look very similar to that of
 the pad with a stiff backing.
 
\end_layout

